## Code vs. Data — Two Licenses

This repository combines source code (MIT, above) with the underlying memorial
dataset, which is separately licensed under
**Creative Commons Attribution-ShareAlike 4.0 International (CC BY-SA 4.0)**.

When you redistribute or build on:

  - The **code** (TypeScript / Python / SQL / configs): the MIT terms above apply.
    Attribution is appreciated but not legally required.

  - The **data** (every victim record, source citation, photo metadata, and
    everything served by `/api/v1/public/dump`, `/api/mcp/*`, `/api/v1/*`):
    CC BY-SA 4.0 applies — you must attribute "Iran Memorial" (github.com/iran-memorial26/iran-memorial)
    and license derivative datasets under the same CC BY-SA 4.0 terms.

Full text of CC BY-SA 4.0: https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/4.0/

If in doubt about which license covers a given file, the rule is:
  - Anything under `prisma/seeds/`, `data/`, exported JSON, exported CSV → CC BY-SA 4.0
  - Anything else → MIT
